OL,3,C'Strong smell of petrol' as NRW
OL,4,Cinvestigates fuel pollution incident
OL,6,FReports were initially made to South
OL,7,FWales Fire and Rescue service which
OL,8,Fthen passed the details of the
OL,9,Fincident onto NRW.
OL,11,FIn a statement NRW says it's "asking
OL,12,Fresidents to please check for any
OL,13,Fleaks from fuel tanks or similar
OL,14,Fsources that could be entering surface
OL,15,Fwater drains.
OL,17,F"Fuelabsorbent booms and pads have
OL,18,Fbeen placed to help contain the
OL,19,Fpollution and we will continue working
OL,20,Ftoday to identify the source as
OL,21,Fquickly as possible.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/3
